# 4. User Roles

## Student

* Register and login.
* Submit assignments.
* View assignment status.
* Resubmit assignments.
* Create or join teams.
* Chat with faculty.
* View comments and feedback.

## Faculty

* Create assignments.
* Approve or reject submissions.
* Provide rejection reasons.
* Reapprove rejected submissions.
* Manage team assignments.
* Export reports.
* Communicate with students.

## Admin

* View all users.
* View all submissions.
* Download reports.
* Monitor activities.
* Manage branches and sections.
* Manage subjects and syllabus.

## Super Admin

* Hidden account reserved for project owner.
* Access complete analytics.
* Manage admins.
* Access audit logs.

---

# 5. Functional Requirements

## Authentication Module

* Role selection during login.
* JWT authentication.
* Forgot password functionality.
* Email verification.
* Password reset via email.

## Student Module

* View assignments.
* Submit assignments.
* Upload multiple file types.
* Add late submission reasons.
* View approval status.
* Team creation and management.
* Real-time chat with faculty.
* Receive email notifications.

## Faculty Module

* Create assignments.
* Specify submission file formats.
* Configure individual or team assignments.
* Configure deadlines.
* Approve or reject submissions.
* Mention rejection reasons.
* Reapprove rejected submissions.
* Bulk approve or reject submissions.
* View pending submission count.

## Admin Module

* View all students branch-wise and section-wise.
* Download reports in Excel or CSV.
* Monitor activities and submissions.
* Access analytics dashboard.
* Manage faculty and students.

## Team Management Module

* Team creation.
* Team invitation.
* Team leader assignment.
* Team leader-only submission permissions.

## Chat Module

* Student-faculty chat.
* Assignment-specific discussions.
* Submission-specific discussion threads.
* Comments section.

## Notification Module

* Approval notifications.
* Rejection notifications.
* Assignment creation notifications.
* Password reset notifications.

## Export Module

* Export submissions.
* Export student activity reports.
* Export approval history.
* Export faculty reports.

